Author::::kjmsisa
DateTime::::2016-03-12T10:02:52Z
My favourite monthly read. Don't know what I'd do without it since The Word bit the dust. WSC isn't just about football, it's as much about the society that football is embedded within. The magazine is no longer about football being marginalised, it is about the marginalisation of things - people, communities, and of course some of the wonderful things about football that we are in danger of losing forever. Yes, the editorialising on the evil of the PL can get a bit tedious and repetitive, and if your are a supporter of one of the 'Big Clubs' it come sometimes be a bit of a bittersweet read. But WSC offers one of those increasingly rare things - a voice of dissent and protest in an increasingly Murdoch-owned, corporatised, and nationalistic world. And it's funny and about football. What's not to like?



